title: NASA Selects Winners, Announces Final Phase of Space Food Challenge
summary: NASA has announced eight winning teams and awarded $750,000 in prizes in the second phase of the agency's Deep Space Food Challenge. The winning teams will move on to compete in the third and final phase of the challenge.

title: NASA selects Blue Origin to develop second Artemis lunar lander
summary: NASA has selected Blue Origin to develop a lunar lander to transport astronauts on Artemis missions starting at the end of the decade.

title: FCC denies Dish Network 5G plan over Starlink interference concerns
summary: U.S. regulators voted May 18 to protect Starlink’s access to 12 GHz spectrum, which Dish Network had hoped to use for terrestrial 5G in a plan SpaceX warned would deny its satellite broadband network to most Americans.

title: NASA Selects Blue Origin as Second Artemis Lunar Lander Provider
summary: To develop a human landing system for the agency’s Artemis V mission to the Moon, NASA has selected Blue Origin of Kent, Washington. Through Artemis, NASA will explore more of the Moon than ever before, uncovering more scientific discoveries, and preparing for future astronaut missions to Mars.

summary: WASHINGTON — Jeff Bezos has his NASA moon ticket.

title: BREAKING! NASA Awards Blue Origin $3.4B Lunar Lander Contract
summary: NASA has selected Blue Origin's new version of Blue Moon for the 2nd Human Landing System contract.

title: Inmarsat orders 3 smallsats to bolster L-band safety services
summary: Inmarsat has ordered three small geostationary satellites from 3D printing specialist Swissto12 for a launch in 2026 to fortify its L-band safety services.
